mal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-09-09T16:33:41.000Z","msg":"finite dimensional space (可以當R^n) 無論你用邊種norm, 唔會影響continuity, convergence呢d性質<br />\n<br />\n但infinute dimensional space會出事<br />\ne.g. C[0, 1] = all real valued continuous functions on [0, 1]<br />\n你會發現用 d(f, g) = max |f(x) - g(x)| 之下個space會&quot;無窿&quot;<br />\n但係用 d(f, g) = \\int_0^1 |f(x) - g(x)| 會&quot;有窿&quot;<br />\n<br />\ne.g. f_n(x) = x^n, 用第二個距離度 f_n 會走左去個窿度<br />\n但用第一種距離度所有function之間都會保持 1 ge距離，唔會炒車 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1e0423865a5450c40fcdf9bf963fa9da6badef8f","tid":812034,"uid":137768,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-09-09T17:01:26.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>咪就係用唔同ge方法量度距離 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n平時果個係我地一般人理解ge距離<br />\n<br />\n唔同距離個重要分別我諗要係infinite dimensional spaces先會見到 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote>咁姐係會見到啲咩<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  ching有無例子<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote>finite dimensional space (可以當R^n) 無論你用邊種norm, 唔會影響continuity, convergence呢d性質<br />\n<br />\n但infinute dimensional space會出事<br />\ne.g. C[0, 1] = all real valued continuous functions on [0, 1]<br />\n你會發現用 d(f, g) = max |f(x) - g(x)| 之下個space會&quot;無窿&quot;<br />\n但係用 d(f, g) = <span style=\"color: red;\">\\int_0^1 </span>|f(x) - g(x)| 會&quot;有窿&quot;<br />\n<br />\ne.g. f_n(x) = x^n, 用第二個距離度 f_n 會走左去個窿度<br />\n但用第一種距離度所有function之間都會保持 1 ge距離，唔會炒車 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\nsorry 睇唔明呢個notation<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1dfdcd72ea92de49448d3c6f23916e9e081e35a6","tid":812034,"uid":11890,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-09T19:33:02.000Z","msg":"用唔同norm做norm/residual minimization時出嘅solution會好唔同<br />\n<br />\n簡單用(3,1)同(1,1)呢兩點 同 (2,2)同(1,1)呢兩點 1-norm距離都係2, 所以(3,1)同(2,2)一樣咁近(1,1)<br />\n但係(3,1)同(1,1)呢兩點2-norm距離係2, 但(2,2)同(1,1)呢兩點2-norm距離就係sqrt(2), 變咗(2,2)比(3,1)更加近(1,1)<br />\n因為(3,1)同(1,1)第一個座標相差大, 二次方個相差就變到更加大<br />\n(2,2)同(1,1)將個相差分散咗, 二次方完都唔會太大<br />\n簡單講句就lp-norm個p越大越會誇大單個座標嘅大差距<br />\n<br />\n例如想minimize ||(x,y)|| subject to x+2y=10<br />\n如果用1-norm會出(0,5)<br />\n如果用2-norm會出(2,4)<br />\n如果用inf-norm會出(10/3,10/3)<br />\n其他p嘅界乎中間唔計啦<br />\n<br />\n應用喺image reconstruction度就有時要minimize in terms of norm of gradient嘅嘢<br />\n用2-norm會reconstruct埋啲逐漸變嘅output, 即係blur咗<br />\n用1-norm就通常會reconstruct到立即變嘅output, 即係幅圖兩件唔同物體之間條界"},{"pid":"ad160fb6b038f491a8f8deab38a6527d61c19e7d","tid":812034,"uid":66324,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"1e0423865a5450c40fcdf9bf963fa9da6badef8f","tid":812034,"uid":137768,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-09-09T17:01:26.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>咪就係用唔同ge方法量度距離 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n平時果個係我地一般人理解ge距離<br />\n<br />\n唔同距離個重要分別我諗要係infinite dimensional spaces先會見到 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote>咁姐係會見到啲咩<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  ching有無例子<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote>finite dimensional space (可以當R^n) 無論你用邊種norm, 唔會影響continuity, convergence呢d性質<br />\n<br />\n但infinute dimensional space會出事<br />\ne.g. C[0, 1] = all real valued continuous functions on [0, 1]<br />\n你會發現用 d(f, g) = max |f(x) - g(x)| 之下個space會&quot;無窿&quot;<br />\n但係用 d(f, g) = <span style=\"color: red;\">\\int_0^1 </span>|f(x) - g(x)| 會&quot;有窿&quot;<br />\n<br />\ne.g. f_n(x) = x^n, 用第二個距離度 f_n 會走左去個窿度<br />\n但用第一種距離度所有function之間都會保持 1 ge距離，唔會炒車 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\nsorry 睇唔明呢個notation<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-09T19:46:25.000Z","msg":"integration from 0 to 1<br />\n<br />\nbtw ckarify少少<br />\n個窿係 f(1) = 1, f(x) = 0 otherwise (呢個function唔係C[0, 1] 呢個世界入面，所以好似個窿咁)<br />\n而第一種方法度，我講緊ge 所有 function 係指 f_n之間"}]}